        "timestamp": "2019-05-13 16:39:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nIf plugin.test and plugin_edgex.sh are the only scripts that uses jq, I suggest to add the instruction in those scripts instead of the installer. IMHO these dependency only has to be present when the functional test are consumed.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8371cbf17cc827bd40985d0e95e461afa4411317",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-13 17:03:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > (1 comment)\n > \n > If plugin.test and plugin_edgex.sh are the only scripts that uses\n > jq, I suggest to add the instruction in those scripts instead of\n > the installer. IMHO these dependency only has to be present when\n > the functional test are consumed.\n\nand also tests/nfd.sh is using it.\n\nI'm cunsuming clean Ubuntu 16.04.6 image for testing and that does not have jq. Those tests/xx.sh files are part of this repo and even run automatically by installer.sh if testing flag enabled. So either installer.sh must install the required package or each test script separately.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "344397e7bad319d86e5668bcd44d3bf38de75552",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 947,
          "name": "Victor Morales",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "chipahuac@hotmail.com",
          "username": "electrocucaracha"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-13 17:25:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > > (1 comment)\n > >\n > > If plugin.test and plugin_edgex.sh are the only scripts that uses\n > > jq, I suggest to add the instruction in those scripts instead of\n > > the installer. IMHO these dependency only has to be present when\n > > the functional test are consumed.\n > \n > and also tests/nfd.sh is using it.\n > \n > I'm cunsuming clean Ubuntu 16.04.6 image for testing and that does\n > not have jq. Those tests/xx.sh files are part of this repo and even\n > run automatically by installer.sh if testing flag enabled. So\n > either installer.sh must install the required package or each test\n > script separately.\n\nSo in that case I suggest to create another script, like _common_test.sh, that collects what's sharing between all the functional tests. Maybe initially only contains one instruction but eventually this can grow.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "7491a5bf97f45ecc990f71fe02f81c425ea7e7c1",
        "author": {
