        "timestamp": "2019-05-13 18:41:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > > > (1 comment)\n > > >\n > > > If plugin.test and plugin_edgex.sh are the only scripts that\n > uses\n > > > jq, I suggest to add the instruction in those scripts instead\n > of\n > > > the installer. IMHO these dependency only has to be present\n > when\n > > > the functional test are consumed.\n > >\n > > and also tests/nfd.sh is using it.\n > >\n > > I'm cunsuming clean Ubuntu 16.04.6 image for testing and that\n > does\n > > not have jq. Those tests/xx.sh files are part of this repo and\n > even\n > > run automatically by installer.sh if testing flag enabled. So\n > > either installer.sh must install the required package or each\n > test\n > > script separately.\n > \n > So in that case I suggest to create another script, like\n > _common_test.sh, that collects what's sharing between all the\n > functional tests. Maybe initially only contains one instruction but\n > eventually this can grow.\n\nOk, can do that.",
        "patchset_number": 2
